\begin_layout Title
Statistics Bridge Introduction to R: Syllabus/schedule
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Subsection*
Comments for presenters
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
40-50 minutes per session for presentation/demo, 20 minutes for breakout
 (including answers)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
try to intersperse little coding questions/challenges within the presentation
 material
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
ask participants to play with code as we go along and see if they can break
 it or tweak it in interesting ways (perhaps reporting this on the bSpace
 forum)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unless otherwise noted, modules are about 75 minutes long: 45 minutes for
 presentation, 20 minutes for breakout and 10 minutes for discussion of
 solutions.
\end_layout

